info.title: Qwary API SDK
info.description:
# API Reference

The Qwary API is **REST-based**. Our API has predictable resource oriented URLs, accepts request bodies and returns responses in **JSON-encoded** format. API uses standard HTTP response codes, authentication and verbs.

You need to request an API SDK access. Click [Here](https://survey.qwary.com/form/S_wSzSPnasH9Wc_FT15X0J1BuEcPl5gI53F_DMZgaao=). 
>Our support team will reach out to you and share client credentials.

post.description: Creates an access token. Use generated token to interact with Qwary APIs.

tags.name: Authentication
tags.description:
The Qwary API uses API Keys to authenticate requests. 

Click [Here](https://survey.qwary.com/form/S_wSzSPnasH9Wc_FT15X0J1BuEcPl5gI53F_DMZgaao=) to request an API Credential for your account. 
>Our support team will reach out to you and share client credentials.

tags.name: Survey
tags.description:
These endpoints lets you create, delete and modify surveys via API. You can also retrieve individual as well as list of your surveys.

A survey needs at least need one page and question in order to record a response.

tags.name: Survey Question
tags.description: The following endpoints let you retrieve and add questions to a default survey page. Add question to a certain survery with POST endpoint including it's surveyId.

tags.name: Campaign
tags.description: The following endpoints let you create email and messaging campaigns.

tags.name: Responses
tags.description: The following endpoints let you ingest responses and view responses via API.
